Aqui temos um comportamento sazonal com trend e nenhum comportamento cclico

  1. For each of the following time series: bricksq, ibmclose, hsales.
  1. Use the preferred forecasting method you identified for that time series in the Exercise Set 2 and apply it to the full data set.
  2. Compute the residuals and plot their ACF. Do the residuals appear to be white noise? What did your forecasting method miss?

bricksq

bricksqfit <- snaive(bricksq, h=27)
plot(bricksqfit)

res <- residuals(bricksqfit)
plot(res)

Acf(res)

Box.test(res, type="Lj")
## 
##  Box-Ljung test
## 
## data:  res
## X-squared = 100.19, df = 1, p-value < 2.2e-16

No, os resduos no parecem ser white-noise.

O mtodo de forecast nao levou em conta a tendncia da srie. (?)

ibmclose

ibmclosefit <- naive(ibmclose, h=30)
plot(ibmclosefit)

res <- residuals(ibmclosefit)
plot(res)

Acf(res)

Box.test(res, type="Lj")
## 
##  Box-Ljung test
## 
## data:  res
## X-squared = 2.717, df = 1, p-value = 0.09929

Sim, os dados parecem ser white-noise e o teste de Ljung confirma isso (p-value > 0.05)
